				%h4 Before you arrive
				%p
					Although weekend traffic can be unforgiving at times, we recommend cabbing around town to maximize the most of your time in Seoul (this CNNGo
					%a{:href => "http://www.cnngo.com/seoul/life/seoul-taxi-guide-783378"} taxi guide
					is helpful). Korean cabs are relatively affordable (just avoid the black “premium” cabs). The only problem with taxis is that most drivers don’t speak English. Fortunately, there’s an app for that. Before you arrive, download the
					%a{:href => "http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/seoul-taxi-guide/id454324478?mt=8"} Seoul Taxi Guide
					on your iOS device. Featuring over 3,000 relevant and popular venues and destinations, this app not only lists and maps out information, it features a handy “taxi card” that tells the driver where you need to go in Korean. If that doesn’t work, provide the street address of your destination. All taxis in Seoul have GPS navigation.							
