			.activity-info.wrapper
				%h4 Zip into Seoul Station on the Airport Express
				%p 
					There’s always weekend traffic in Seoul, and this is especially true in the month of November as Seoulites head to the countryside to enjoy the last stretch of fall foliage. The best way to maximize your time in the city is by taking the newly-constructed Airport Railroad (AREX), a speedy rail service on the B1 floor of the airport’s Transportation Center. The Express train that runs every 30 minutes will bring you to the heart of Seoul (Seoul Station) in 43 minutes for 13,300 won (alternately, regular Commuter trains take only 10 more minutes but cost a mere 3,700 won). See the timetable and more information
					%a{:href => "http://english.arex.or.kr/jsp/eng/index.jsp"} here
					and an overview at the Incheon Airport
					= succeed "." do
						%a{:href => "http://www.airport.kr/iiacms/pageWork.iia?_scode=C1203020000&fake=1237351365898"} website
