				%h4 Choose your own palatial adventure				
				%img{:src => "images/seoul-safari_03.jpg"}
				%blockquote “We will be tired with lack of sleep, so something that will be fast-paced and keeps us going would be great!”
				%p
					Most first-time visitors to Seoul get the royal treatment at
					= succeed "," do
						%a{:href => "http://www.royalpalace.go.kr/html/eng/main/main.jsp"} Gyeongbok Palace
					the largest of the Five Grand Palaces of the Joseon Dynasty, but we also love the smaller and perhaps more alluring
					= succeed "." do
						%a{:href => "http://eng.cdg.go.kr/main/main.htm"} Changdeokgung
					If you decide on Changdeok Palace, don’t miss the lush landscape and lotus pond located behind the palace at the
					= succeed "," do
						%em.inline Biwon
					or Secret Garden. It’s criss-crossed with long walking paths perfect for both meandering and brisk walks.
