			.activity-info.wrapper
				%h4 Freshen up for the long haul home
				%p
					From spas to movie rooms, there are
					%a{:href => "http://www.airport.kr/iiacms/pageWork.iia?_scode=C1202020400&fake=1237265756305"} multiple amenities
					catering to the transit passengers at Incheon International Airport, but our favorite?
					= succeed "." do
						%a{:href => "http://www.wellss.com/new/wellss_service_shower.htm."} Complimentary showers
					You’ll have time to kill after checking in early, so take this time to freshen up in these spacious, marble-lined rooms equipped with a sink, toilet and small vanity space (no wonder they’re so popular among Korean couples en route to their honeymoons). Before the long haul home, step into the separated walk-in shower and relax under the sunflower shower head. Remember to pack shower supplies in your carry-on; face towels are complimentary while bath towel rentals and a shower kit (shampoo, conditioner, soap and razor) can be purchased at 4 dollars each. Open 7 a.m. to around 9 p.m. daily. For a more comprehensive list of services, indulge yourself at the
					= succeed "," do
						%a{:href => "http://english.visitkorea.or.kr/enu/FU/FU_EN_15.jsp?cid=637127"} Hub Lounge
					where a premium lounge experience can be purchased for $35 USD. See an extensive list of airport goodies
					= succeed "." do
						%a{:href => "http://visitkorea.or.kr/enu/SI/SI_EN_3_6.jsp?cid=258029"} here
				%p Have a safe flight home!
